## Step-by-Step Guide

1. Install Ansible: on your local machine.
```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible
```

2. Create an Ansible Inventory File:
<br>This file will contain the connection details for your Proxmox server.

3. Create a file named inventory.ini:
```
[proxmox]
192.168.88.15 ansible_user=starmark ansible_password=4e8uRu55k@ ansible_become=yes ansible_become_method=sudo
```

4. Create an Ansible Playbook: This playbook will define the tasks to create and configure the VM.
<br>Create a file named create_vm.yml:
```
---
- name: Create and configure VM on Proxmox
  hosts: proxmox
  tasks:
    - name: Create VM
      proxmox_kvm:
        api_user: "starmark@pve"
        api_password: "4e8uRu55k@"
        api_host: "192.168.88.15"
        node: "MonDuck"  # Replace with your actual node name
        vmid: 6005
        name: "Devel"
        memory: 8192
        cores: 4
        sockets: 1
        disk: 400
        storage: "local-lvm"  # Adjust storage as needed
        iso: "local:iso/ubuntu-22.04.5-live-server-amd64.iso"  # Adjust ISO path as needed
        net0: "virtio,bridge=vmbr0"
        ostype: "l26"
        onboot: true
        boot: "cdn"
        scsihw: "virtio-scsi-pci"
        state: present
```

5. Установка sshpass
```
sudo apt update
sudo apt install sshpass
```

6. Run the Ansible Playbook:
<br>Execute the playbook to create the VM.
```
ansible-playbook -i inventory.ini create_vm.yml
```